1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:09,400
SessionPorter: turn one AI coding session into a portable, privacy-aware bundle. Local-first, sanitized by default, no external AI.

2
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:29,400
AI sessions are useful development evidence but contain secrets and private paths, and every tool stores them differently.

3
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:46,400
Discover lists sessions: metadata only, no content, no full paths.

4
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:58,400
Inspect one selected session by its safe, hashed id.

5
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:14,400
Preview redactions before anything is written. The report shows counts only, never values.

6
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:30,400
Export writes the bundle. Sanitized is the default; private mode requires an explicit confirmation.

7
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:44,400
The bundle: normalized.jsonl goes to AgentTrace; transcript.md goes to an offline Claude conversation; no raw log in sanitized mode.

8
00:01:44,400 --> 00:02:00,400
The transcript carries an honest completeness note. Hidden model reasoning is not reconstructed.

9
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:16,400
The redaction report lists category, count, and affected events only. It never prints a value.

10
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:38,400
Every bundle is validated by checksums. A test proves zero network egress. Records are exported, never executed.

11
00:02:38,400 --> 00:03:04,400
Built with Claude Code and review subagents. A portability subagent found AgentTrace ignores a flat category, so the output became AgentTrace-native records.

12
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:22,400
Local CLI, no database, no cloud, no external model. Codex is experimental. Current-session matching is heuristic. Redaction is heuristic, so review before sharing.

13
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:34,400
SessionPorter turns one selected AI coding session into a portable, validated, privacy-aware evidence bundle.
